  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then, when I was asked to no longer see my Christian boyfriend, when his mother asked me-- or asked my mother-- to stop having him visit or me visiting their house, then I felt very down and felt, 'everything is struggle, unspeakable, unbearably difficult struggle.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we have to fight it through.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We have to hold on and continue,' in quotes, 'wound covered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We, the chosen, the strong sufferers, the bearers of new forces.' And then I wrote a poem.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I have translated the poem.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'Mother, life is too hard to bear.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mother, I want to give up and cry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mother, my strength is no longer there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mother, make it easy for me to die.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What is holding me?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not humanity, not the world, but the all powerful which held together.'",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For those of you, written by Goethe, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I felt that was too much for-- I was 19 at that time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I will comment that all my friends had become Nazis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's-- these are things that I had found in-- in my mother's possession.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had rescued two-- two of my diaries.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She had brought them out of Germany, because we couldn't bring much else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We brought books and some furniture and-- talking about books, my mother and I-- when we were-- when we were packing the last week when I came home from Switzerland-- we-- my mother and I, with tears in our eyes, we burnt all our books by Russian authors, because we knew that the people-- we had Gestapo, the secret police in the house while we were packing-- that they would think that we were communist if they saw a Russian name like Tolstoy or Dostoevsky.",
      "word_count": 85
    }
  ],
